      • VoiceMessageRequest

        public VoiceMessageRequest()

      • VoiceMessageRequest

        public VoiceMessageRequest(int offset,
                   java.lang.String fileName,
                   int fileSize,
                   byte[] audioStream,
                   java.lang.String fromUser,
                   java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> toUser,
                   java.lang.String requestType,
                   java.lang.String message)
        Create a voice message request. offset is the offset position of the whole audio stream buffer. filename tell the receiver where to store file. filesize is the whole size of voice message file will send. fromUser is the name of user who sent this request. toUsers is an Arraylist that store all users wants to send to. requestType is to identify this request's type, which including GET_ALL_USERSNAME, client asks to get all online usersname from server. SERVER_ALL_USERSNAME, server responses clients a list of online username in toUser Arraylist. REMOVE_MY_USERNAME, client asks to remove its name from server and do self disconnection. VOICE_MESSAGE, notices client and server that this request includes voice stream data. CHAT_MESSAGE, notices client and server that this request has chat message data.
        Parameters:
        offset - the offset position of the whole audio stream buffer.
        fileName - the file name for saving audio file.
        fileSize - the total size of voice message will send.
        audioStream - the audio stream data.
        fromUser - the name of user who sent this request.
        toUser - the name of list users who will receive this request.
        requestType - identify this request in different types.
        message - additional message to notices users.
